Text: More than $100 million has been raked back from welfare cheats who were dobbed in, Federal government frontbencher Stuart Robert says. The Department of Human Services received more than 90,000 tip offs from the public about welfare, Medicare and Child Support fraud in the 2018/19 financial year which has led to 200 investigations.
